Quick comment, I cringe when people average OEE for the Line like this. For this case it's correct because the time is the same, 2 hrs. But usually it's not. You should work out each line component e.g. total run time and total time of the two machines to work out the line A then P the Q then work out the line OEE to be correct.
I know you know this, just for the benefit of other ppl.

@r.pop already mentioned the OEE by part number. Great. Also you can do it by Work Order or Production runs (aka lot . This is each segment of the Work Order that was done. e.g. in one shift by product but can be finer if there's a lot of changeover)

